Er, try 3k-4.5k. Any wizi at 60 with less than 3k is running around nekkid. Best I personally know is 4700 mana. Hell, my wizi is only 55 and I already hit 3k, and I don't even have uber wallpaper. I did eat an uber sandwhich once, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/02 5:28:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=94>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Team Manaburn...blessing or Curse?</span><hr size=1> ROFL.  <br>
<br>
MB does and doesn't help mid level guilds.  These guilds can't organize and group at the speed at which a team of MB wizards can.  It's also very discouraging to these guilds.  Why try to even race when MB wizzies get there faster almost always?  A bigger guild can beat MB wizzies, but that's because of organization.  Now, if the guild gets an MB wizard or two, these guys could join the MB team and get what the guild needs...that's the way I see it helping these guilds.  Yes, they could help their guild kill the mob, but chances for that are considerably more limited and you still have all the organizational hassles.  Much easier to cut your wizard free on a mission to get your guild the epic pieces it needs.<br>
<br>
Yes, other small number of people can kill these dragons.  But they require some pretty nice gear to do so.  A much larger time investment than a piddly amount of AA (yes, the amount to get MB isn't that much, especially if you want to compare it to the time it takes to get gear to match Furor's).  Additionally, those other small groups of people still need some balance.  Those people also take longer to organize and buff.<br>
<br>
The MB issue is only going to get worse.  Don't bother giving crap like that there aren't enough MB wizzies and they are all in uber guilds.  There are plenty and more and more of them aren't in uber guilds.  All it takes to get MB is time.  These newer MB wizards aren't going to be tied up in guild raids on patch day.  MB (combined with the power of wizards vs high end mobs) will draw more people to the class.  Some people like to say &quot;if you are so jealous, make a wizard and get MB&quot;...their logic being that people will see how much work it is.  Guess what, people are making wizards and like any other class, wizards can be easily powered (group with a melee or else run some varition of beat down/mem blur).  Wizards can now be twinked much like melees...slap a KEI, an FT item, some focus items and watch them go.<br>
<br>
Anyway, to me, there's nothing wrong with MB in principle (PvE-wise).  What is wrong is what is mana burnable.  It shouldn't be Gorenaire, Talendor, and Sev.  These dragons are important to people for their epic drops and haste.  Wuoshi and most others?  Who cares?<br>
<br>
Simple enough solution: leave the existing dragons as they are and add a spawnable epic version for them, like they've done with ranger and druid epics.<br>
